# ADR-0001: Tier selection — {{tier}}

**Status:** Accepted
**Date:** {{date}}
**Decider:** <author name>

## Context

This project was initialized with `workshop init {{project_name}} --tier {{tier}}`. The framework's tier system (production / standard / sketch) configures defaults based on **risk profile**, not project size or category.

## Decision

The project starts on **{{tier}} tier**. This sets the framework defaults documented in `framework.config.toml`. Tier promotion (`workshop promote --to <tier>`) is supported when the project's risk profile increases. Demotion is intentionally not supported.

## Why this tier

<Replace this paragraph with the actual rationale for the tier choice. Examples:

- **Production:** "Real users, real money, real consequences. The system handles payment data and is publicly deployed."
- **Standard:** "Personal serious project. I'll keep using it but it's not shipping publicly. Discipline is advisory."
- **Sketch:** "Throwaway experiment. Iterating fast on an idea; will likely delete in a week.">

## Consequences

- Framework defaults set per the tier — see `framework.config.toml` for the actual values
- Tier-specific gates apply (see workshop-level CLAUDE.md and project CLAUDE.md)
- Promotion is additive and supported (`workshop promote --to <tier>`); demotion is not
- The plan template, hook behavior, learning module, and review trigger all read this tier setting

